Paragraph

A paragraph (from the Greek paragraphos, "to write beside" or "written beside") is a self-contained unit of a discourse in writing dealing with a particular point or idea. A paragraph consists of one or more sentences. Though not required by the syntax of any language, paragraphs are usually an expected part of formal writing, used to organize longer prose.

HTML

									
										<p>A paragraph (from the Greek paragraphos, "to write beside" or "written beside") is a self-contained unit of a discourse in writing dealing with a particular point or idea. A paragraph consists of one or more sentences. Though not required by the syntax of any language, paragraphs are usually an expected part of formal writing, used to organize longer prose.</p>

Blockquote

A block quotation (also known as a long quotation or extract) is a quotation in a written document, that is set off from the main text as a paragraph, or block of text, and typically distinguished visually using indentation and a different typeface or smaller size quotation.

HTML

									
										<blockquote>
	<p>A block quotation (also known as a long quotation or extract) is a quotation in a written document, that is set off from the main text as a paragraph, or block of text, and typically distinguished visually using indentation and a different typeface or smaller size quotation.</p>
</blockquote>

Inline Elements

This is a text link

Strong is used to indicate strong importance

This text has added emphasis

The b element is stylistically different text from normal text, without any special importance

The i element is text that is set off from the normal text

The u element is text with an unarticulated, though explicitly rendered, non-textual annotation

This text is deleted and This text is inserted

This text has a strikethrough

Superscript®

Subscript for things like H2O

This small text is small for for fine print, etc.

Abbreviation: HTML

Keybord input: Cmd

This text is a short inline quotation

This is a citation

The dfn element indicates a definition.

The mark element indicates a highlight

This is what inline code looks like.

This is sample output from a computer program

The variable element, such as x = y

HTML

									
										<div class="text">
	<p><a href="#">This is a text link</a></p>

	<p><strong>Strong is used to indicate strong importance</strong></p>

	<p><em>This text has added emphasis</em></p>

	<p>The <b>b element</b> is stylistically different text from normal text, without any special importance</p>

	<p>The <i>i element</i> is text that is set off from the normal text</p>

	<p>The <u>u element</u> is text with an unarticulated, though explicitly rendered, non-textual annotation</p>

	<p><del>This text is deleted</del> and <ins>This text is inserted</ins></p>

	<p><s>This text has a strikethrough</s></p>

	<p>Superscript<sup>®</sup></p>

	<p>Subscript for things like H<sub>2</sub>O</p>

	<p><small>This small text is small for for fine print, etc.</small></p>

	<p>Abbreviation: <abbr title="HyperText Markup Language">HTML</abbr></p>

	<p>Keybord input: <kbd>Cmd</kbd></p>

	<p><q cite="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/HTML/Element/q">This text is a short inline quotation</q></p>

	<p><cite>This is a citation</cite>

	</p><p>The <dfn>dfn element</dfn> indicates a definition.</p>

	<p>The <mark>mark element</mark> indicates a highlight</p>

	<p><code>This is what inline code looks like.</code></p>

	<p><samp>This is sample output from a computer program</samp></p>

	<p>The <var>variable element</var>, such as <var>x</var> = <var>y</var></p>
</div><!--end .text-->

Unordered

  • This is a list item in an unordered list
  • An unordered list is a list in which the sequence of items is not important. Sometimes, an unordered list is a bulleted list. And this is a long list item in an unordered list that can wrap onto a new line.
  • Lists can be nested inside of each other
    • This is a nested list item
    • This is another nested list item in an unordered list
  • This is the last list item

HTML

									
										<div class="text">
	<ul>
		<li>This is a list item in an unordered list</li>
		<li>An unordered list is a list in which the sequence of items is not important. Sometimes, an unordered list is a bulleted list. And this is a long list item in an unordered list that can wrap onto a new line. </li>
		<li>
			Lists can be nested inside of each other
			<ul>
				<li>This is a nested list item</li>
				<li>This is another nested list item in an unordered list</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>This is the last list item</li>
	</ul>
</div>

Ordered

  1. This is a list item in an ordered list
  2. An ordered list is a list in which the sequence of items is important. An ordered list does not necessarily contain sequence characters.
  3. Lists can be nested inside of each other
    1. This is a nested list item
    2. This is another nested list item in an ordered list
  4. This is the last list item

HTML

									
										<div class="text">
	<ol>
		<li>This is a list item in an ordered list</li>
		<li>An ordered list is a list in which the sequence of items is important. An ordered list does not necessarily contain sequence characters.</li>
		<li>
			Lists can be nested inside of each other
			<ol>
				<li>This is a nested list item</li>
				<li>This is another nested list item in an ordered list</li>
			</ol>
		</li>
		<li>This is the last list item</li>
	</ol>
</div>

Definition

Definition List
A number of connected items or names written or printed consecutively, typically one below the other.
This is a term.
This is the definition of that term, which both live in a dl.
Here is another term.
And it gets a definition too, which is this line.
Here is term that shares a definition with the term below.
And it gets a definition too, which is this line.

HTML

									
										<dl>
	<dt>Definition List</dt>
	<dd>A number of connected items or names written or printed consecutively, typically one below the other.</dd>
    <dt>This is a term.</dt>
    <dd>This is the definition of that term, which both live in a <code>dl</code>.</dd>
    <dt>Here is another term.</dt>
    <dd>And it gets a definition too, which is this line.</dd>
    <dt>Here is term that shares a definition with the term below.</dt>
    <dd>And it gets a definition too, which is this line.</dd>
</dl>

Blockquote With Citation

A block quotation (also known as a long quotation or extract) is a quotation in a written document, that is set off from the main text as a paragraph, or block of text, and typically distinguished visually using indentation and a different typeface or smaller size quotation.

Quote Source

HTML

									
										<blockquote>
   	<p>A block quotation (also known as a long quotation or extract) is a quotation in a written document, that is set off from the main text as a paragraph, or block of text, and typically distinguished visually using indentation and a different typeface or smaller size quotation. </p>
	<cite class="citation">Quote Source</cite>
</blockquote>

    Assessment Tips

    Tips

    1. The assessment is best on a desktop computer.
    2. Set aside 40 minutes to complete.
    3. If you need to scroll within the assessment, move your cursor into the frame.
    4. Progress is auto-saved at the end of each section.
    5. Starting and stopping is OK.

    HTML

    									
										<div class="main-box clearfix">
    <header class="main-box-header clearfix">
        <h2>Tips</h2>
    </header>

    <div class="main-box-body clearfix">
        <ol>
            <li>The assessment is best on a desktop computer.</li>
            <li>Set aside 40 minutes to complete.</li>
            <li>If you need to scroll within the assessment, move your cursor into the frame.</li>
            <li>Progress is auto-saved at the end of each section.</li>
            <li>Starting and stopping is OK.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</div>

    Job Detail

    Marketing Manager

    Location:
    St. Louis, MO
    Company:
    Hallmark Cards
    Minimum Experience:
    1
    Match Score:
    95%

    Apply

    The Creative Marketing Studio within Hallmark Cards is an in-house agency respected by clients and organizations inside and outside of Hallmark’s headquarters. It is comprised of Hallmark brand experts who deliver strategic, award-winning work that directly influences the company’s bottom line. We’re looking for talented creative professionals who want to help create an experience that will make everyone fall in love with the Hallmark brand. We are responsible for brand building, creative leadership and consumer activation, including:

    • Cross-channel marketing campaigns (such as print, digital, direct, videos and content)
    • Brand direction for Hallmark marketing across channels (packaging, marketing, visual merchandising, digital)
    • Naming and tagline exploration for new products and services from Hallmark and its sub brands
    • Collateral development for internal departments, including Brand Management and Corporate Recruiting
    • Creative projects for a variety of internal and external businesses and initiatives

    Functional Statement Title/#: Marketing Manager, GS-679-5

    Location:
    St. Louis, MO
    Company:
    Hallmark Cards
    Minimum Experience:
    1
    Match Score:
    95%

    Job Lead 1 of 11


    Email Marketing Manager

    San Franciso, CA - Uber Technologies


    They're looking for: Experience creating and launching email campaigns using a leading ESP such as ExactTarget and SendGrid.

    I'll be responsible for: Developing email marketing strategies that engage millions of users across the globe.

    I'll also be responsible for: Set-uping and deploying complex automated communications within ExactTarget and SendGrid

    I can expect to make: $59,600 Annual

    Better Weekdays Pattern Lab

    • Personal Motivators
    • Area Missions

    2 / 8 sections completed.

    25% Complete

    Tips

    1. The assessment is best on a desktop computer.
    2. Set aside 40 minutes to complete.
    3. If you need to scroll within the assessment, move your cursor into the frame.
    4. Progress is auto-saved at the end of each section.
    5. Starting and stopping is OK.

    Better Weekdays Pattern Lab

    Jobs Available 827,459
    Jobs Added Yesterday 7,301
    Companies 81,305

    What Should I Do Next?

    • Now
    • View at least 5 jobs in playlist view
    • Did you actually apply to the Email Marketing Manager job at Uber Technologies?
    • Send thank-you note to Uber Technologies for interview (why?)
    • Next Week
    • Log back in and check for new matches (why?)
    • Research salary of position (why?)

    Choose Your Better Weekday

      Leads

    Quickly view jobs without a resume.

    Best for jobs with a specific title or certification.

      Matches

    Discover new careers at established companies automatically refreshed daily.

    Requires a resume and an idea of location preference.

      Assessment

    Gain scientific insight into your leadership potential.

    Takes about 30 minutes.

      Guarantees

    2. Email Marketing Manager

    Email Marketing Manager

    Company

    Uber Technologies

    • Formed: 2009
    • Industry: Internet
    • Employees: 1,000-5,000
    • Website
    • Wikipedia
    • Google Plus

    Location

    San Franciso, CA

    • Population: 852,469
    • Avg. Monthly Salary: $3,694.98
    • Mediterranean Climate
    • Events
    • Points of Interest
    • Neighborhoods

    Schedule

    40hr Week

    • 8 hr days
    • 5 days per week
    • 3 weeks time off
    • Vacation Policy
    • Sick / Personal Day Policy

    Compensation

    $59,600 Annual

    • $3,256 Monthly
    • $35.40 Hourly
    • You
    • The Job
    • What It's Like
    • Develop email marketing strategies that engage millions of users across the globe.
    • Set-up and deploy complex automated communications within ExactTarget and SendGrid
    • Ensure email messaging is 100% accessible to everyone on both web and mobile.
    • Manage schedule of deployment to optimize user response and actively manage email lists.
    • Generate, analyze, and interpret data for email campaigns.
    • Work closely with our policy, communications, product, and business development teams for strategic campaigns.
    • Build structures, process, and guidance for local marketing teams operating in cities around the world.

    Uber is evolving the way the world moves. By seamlessly connecting riders to drivers through our apps, we make cities more accessible, opening up more possibilities for riders and more business for drivers. We're a game-changing startup, providing quality, on-demand car requests from the touch of your phone. A tenacity toward delivering an awesome experience for our users is critical to our success, and we're looking for an email marketing rock star to help bolster Uber’s brand presence through highly-polished, data-driven email communications campaigns. As member of a cross-functional email marketing team, the right person will be comfortable in an "all hands on deck" environment, able to operate and coordinate across multiple teams, and can thrive in a startup culture. This role is all about communicating Uber and the brand to the masses. You should be a proven innovator and email expert, ready to build Uber email campaigns that can match our rapidly growing global brand.

    • Employees are showered with Uber credits each month.
    • The rare opportunity to change the world such that everyone around you is using the product you built. We’re not just another social web app, we’re moving real people and assets and reinventing transportation and logistics globally.
    • Sharp, motivated co-workers in a fun office environment.

    © 2015 Better Weekdays. All rights reserved.

<li>Develop email marketing strategies that engage millions of users across the globe.</li>
<li>Set-up and deploy complex automated communications within ExactTarget and SendGrid</li>
<li>Ensure email messaging is 100% accessible to everyone on both web and mobile.</li>
<li>Manage schedule of deployment to optimize user response and actively manage email lists.</li>

<li>Build structures, process, and guidance for local marketing teams operating in cities around the world.</li>
</ul></div>

                                                            <p>Uber is evolving the way the world moves. By seamlessly connecting riders to drivers through our apps, we make cities more accessible, opening up more possibilities for riders and more business for drivers. We're a game-changing startup, providing quality, on-demand car requests from the touch of your phone. A tenacity toward delivering an awesome experience for our users is critical to our success, and we're looking for an email marketing rock star to help bolster Uber’s brand presence through highly-polished, data-driven email communications campaigns.
 
As member of a cross-functional email marketing team, the right person will be comfortable in an "all hands on deck" environment, able to operate and coordinate across multiple teams, and can thrive in a startup culture. This role is all about communicating Uber and the brand to the masses. You should be a proven innovator and email expert, ready to build Uber email campaigns that can match our rapidly growing global brand.</p>

<li>Sharp, motivated co-workers in a fun office environment.</li>
</ul></div>

    Better Weekdays Pattern Lab

    Marketing Manager

    Location:
    St. Louis, MO
    Company:
    Hallmark Cards
    Minimum Experience:
    1
    Match Score:
    95%

    Apply

    This position is located in PCS/Clinical Support Service. Incumbent in this roles will be responsible for performing a variety of administrative and clerical duties and is the liaison between the nursing staff in their assigned area and customers both internal and external to the medical center.

    Specialized experience includes, but is not limited, to the following:

    • Scheduling, canceling and rescheduling patients discharge appointments.
    • Accurately and timely processing patient information, admits, discharge, appointments and transfers in computer system.
    • Arranging and coordinating in-patient procedure appointments for timeliness.
    • Maintaining office supplies.
    • Providing professional and courteous customer service.
    • Assisting with the orientation/on the job training of new staff.
    • Completing work orders and contacting appropriate staff when requested for emergency repairs or special requests.
    • Inputting and extracting data of a highly technical nature.
    • Interpreting and transcribing doctors orders.
    • Maintaining patient records, scanning, quality control

    Work Schedule: 2 shifts available

    SHIFT 1: 7:30AM  4:00PM, Monday through Friday working every THIRD weekend with rotating holidays. Note: Dayshift position will provide backup coverage to Decedent Affairs, duties include but not limited to releasing deceased veterans to funeral homes, updating patient deaths, providing information regarding death benefits, updating Advance Directive information in patient records.

    SHIFT 2: 3:30PM  12Midnight, Monday-Friday working every OTHER weekend with rotating holidays.

    Functional Statement Title/#: Marketing Manager, GS-679-5

    Location:
    St. Louis, MO
    Company:
    Hallmark Cards
    Minimum Experience:
    1
    Match Score:
    95%

    Apply

    Brand Design - Beats by Dr. Dre

    BDubs Bot

    Job Lead 2 of 11


    Brand Design - Beats by Dr. Dre

    Culver City, CA - Apple, Inc.


    They're looking for: A student of consumers. Of trends, competitors and culture.

    I'll be responsible for: Design and deliver extraordinary brand marketing creative across all virtual and tangible spaces.

    I'll also be responsible for: Gather and tell stories that compel consumers to seek out Beats products.

    I can expect to make: $56,235


    People who work here say: There are limitless advancement opportunities. You work with some very cool people and the leadership cares about your development.

    They also say: The pay is excellent but the environment can be very stressful. Management is mostly competent and helpful, but a few bad eggs do make it through.

    The cost of living is about: $2.80/gal for gas, $1400/mo for rent (900 sq. ft), and $33 to go to dinner for two

    I may be promoted to: Senior Brand Executive

    powered by


    Hint: Choosing 'Me' or 'Not Me' shows the next job lead.

    Email Marketing Manager

    BDubs Bot

    Job Lead 1 of 11


    Email Marketing Manager

    San Franciso, CA - Uber Technologies


    They're looking for: Experience creating and launching email campaigns using a leading ESP such as ExactTarget and SendGrid.

    I'll be responsible for: Developing email marketing strategies that engage millions of users across the globe.

    I'll also be responsible for: Set-uping and deploying complex automated communications within ExactTarget and SendGrid

    I can expect to make: $59,600 Annual


    People who work here say: Super talented people are flocking to Uber from the Bay Area's top tech companies - Things move so much faster here than anywhere else I've worked - you'll be able to get much more done - Legitimately changing the world.

    They also say: Long hours (but if they feel like work, you're doing something wrong).

    The cost of living is about: $2.80/gal for gas, $1400/mo for rent (900 sq. ft), and $33 to go to dinner for two

    I may be promoted to: Senior Marketing Executive

    powered by


    Hint: Choosing 'Me' or 'Not Me' shows the next job lead.

    Frequently Asked Questions

    Helpful Student Engagement Tips

    What's the best way to follow-up with employers once connected?

    Follow up with thank-you notes to employers, preferably a hand written letter or postcard rather than an email.

    What is the most important step when establishing employer relationships?

    When approaching a potential partner, be sure to explain how the employer will benefit such as making valuable new connections, promoting their brand, and gaining access to potential employees.

    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-xs-12">
                <div id="login-box">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-xs-12">
                            <header id="login-header">
                                <div id="login-logo">
                                    <img src="http://wwwcc.ivytech.edu/northeast/marketing/assets/IVY_HZ_C.jpg" alt=""/>

    Self-Assessment

    JobScript Assessment

    The JobScript Assessment will help provide clarity along your career journey. It will also help us match you with jobs based on your culture preferences.

    The Action Plan will help provide concrete next steps as you progress through your career journey.

    Self-Assessment

    Progress

    • Personal Motivators
    • Area Missions

    2 / 8 sections completed.

    25% Complete

    Tips

    1. The assessment is best on a desktop computer.
    2. Set aside 40 minutes to complete.
    3. If you need to scroll within the assessment, move your cursor into the frame.
    4. Progress is auto-saved at the end of each section.
    5. Starting and stopping is OK.

    Learn

    Learn to Interview

    An interview is a conversation between you and an employer. It is your opportunity to convince a potential employer that you are the right person for the position.

    Source: Wake Forest University

    Preparing for the Job Search

    A job search involves more than one strategy to communicate with prospective employers. Some industries favor the use of some strategies over others. Review all of the strategies to determine which works best for your field. No matter your interest, networking remains one of the top strategies. As you engage in the various job search strategies, consider working with a career counselor as your job search coach.

    Source: Penn State

    Writing Cover Letters (PDF)

    An effective cover letter inspires the employer to read your resume. The cover letter should show that you are familiar with the organization and should emphasize how your experience meets the employer's needs. Communication skills, attention to detail, enthusiasm, and style are all demonstrated through a well-written letter. A cover letter should not re-state what you list on your resume but rather should show how your skills make you a good match for the position.

    Source: Clark University

    Quickly view jobs without a resume.

    Best for jobs with a specific title or certification.

    Discover new careers at established companies automatically refreshed daily.

    Requires a resume and an idea of location preference.

    Helpful Articles

    Learn to Interview

    An interview is a conversation between you and an employer. It is your opportunity to convince a potential employer that you are the right person for the position.

    Source: Wake Forest University

    Preparing for the Job Search

    A job search involves more than one strategy to communicate with prospective employers. Some industries favor the use of some strategies over others. Review all of the strategies to determine which works best for your field. No matter your interest, networking remains one of the top strategies. As you engage in the various job search strategies, consider working with a career counselor as your job search coach.

    Source: Penn State

    Writing Cover Letters (PDF)

    An effective cover letter inspires the employer to read your resume. The cover letter should show that you are familiar with the organization and should emphasize how your experience meets the employer's needs. Communication skills, attention to detail, enthusiasm, and style are all demonstrated through a well-written letter. A cover letter should not re-state what you list on your resume but rather should show how your skills make you a good match for the position.

    Source: Clark University

                                        <a href="http://career.opcd.wfu.edu/practice-for-an-interview/ " class="list-group-item">
                                            <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Learn to Interview</h4>
                                            <p class="list-group-item-text">An interview is a conversation between you and an employer. It is your opportunity to convince a potential employer that you are the right person for the position.</p>
                                            <p class="small">Source: Wake Forest University</p>
                                        </a>
                                        <a href="http://studentaffairs.psu.edu/career/students/job_search.shtml " class="list-group-item">
                                            <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Preparing for the Job Search</h4>
                                            <p class="list-group-item-text">A job search involves more than one strategy to communicate with prospective employers. Some industries favor the use of some strategies over others. Review all of the strategies to determine which works best for your field. No matter your interest, networking remains one of the top strategies. As you engage in the various job search strategies, consider working with a career counselor as your job search coach.</p>
                                            <p class="small">Source: Penn State</p>
                                        </a>
                                        <a href="http://www.clarku.edu/offices/career/students/pdf/CoverLetterhandoutnewheading.pdf " class="list-group-item">
                                            <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Writing Cover Letters (PDF)</h4>
                                            <p class="list-group-item-text">An effective cover letter inspires the employer to read your resume. The cover letter should show that you are familiar with the organization and should emphasize how your experience meets the employer's needs. Communication skills, attention to detail, enthusiasm, and style are all demonstrated through a well-written letter. A cover letter should not re-state what you list on your resume but rather should show how your skills make you a good match for the position.</p>
                                            <p class="small">Source: Clark University</p>
                                        </a>

    Email Marketing Manager

    Company

    Uber Technologies

    • Formed: 2009
    • Industry: Internet
    • Employees: 1,000-5,000
    • Website
    • Wikipedia
    • Google Plus

    Location

    San Franciso, CA

    • Population: 852,469
    • Avg. Monthly Salary: $3,694.98
    • Mediterranean Climate
    • Events
    • Points of Interest
    • Neighborhoods

    Schedule

    40hr Week

    • 8 hr days
    • 5 days per week
    • 3 weeks time off
    • Vacation Policy
    • Sick / Personal Day Policy

    Compensation

    $59,600 Annual

    • $3,256 Monthly
    • $35.40 Hourly
    • You
    • The Job
    • What It's Like
    • Develop email marketing strategies that engage millions of users across the globe.
    • Set-up and deploy complex automated communications within ExactTarget and SendGrid
    • Ensure email messaging is 100% accessible to everyone on both web and mobile.
    • Manage schedule of deployment to optimize user response and actively manage email lists.
    • Generate, analyze, and interpret data for email campaigns.
    • Work closely with our policy, communications, product, and business development teams for strategic campaigns.
    • Build structures, process, and guidance for local marketing teams operating in cities around the world.

    Uber is evolving the way the world moves. By seamlessly connecting riders to drivers through our apps, we make cities more accessible, opening up more possibilities for riders and more business for drivers. We're a game-changing startup, providing quality, on-demand car requests from the touch of your phone. A tenacity toward delivering an awesome experience for our users is critical to our success, and we're looking for an email marketing rock star to help bolster Uber’s brand presence through highly-polished, data-driven email communications campaigns. As member of a cross-functional email marketing team, the right person will be comfortable in an "all hands on deck" environment, able to operate and coordinate across multiple teams, and can thrive in a startup culture. This role is all about communicating Uber and the brand to the masses. You should be a proven innovator and email expert, ready to build Uber email campaigns that can match our rapidly growing global brand.

    • Employees are showered with Uber credits each month.
    • The rare opportunity to change the world such that everyone around you is using the product you built. We’re not just another social web app, we’re moving real people and assets and reinventing transportation and logistics globally.
    • Sharp, motivated co-workers in a fun office environment.

    © 2015 Better Weekdays. All rights reserved.

    Marketing Manager

    Marketing Manager

    Location:
    St. Louis, MO
    Company:
    Hallmark Cards
    Minimum Experience:
    1
    Match Score:
    95%

    Apply

    This position is located in PCS/Clinical Support Service. Incumbent in this roles will be responsible for performing a variety of administrative and clerical duties and is the liaison between the nursing staff in their assigned area and customers both internal and external to the medical center.

    Specialized experience includes, but is not limited, to the following:

    • Scheduling, canceling and rescheduling patients discharge appointments.
    • Accurately and timely processing patient information, admits, discharge, appointments and transfers in computer system.
    • Arranging and coordinating in-patient procedure appointments for timeliness.
    • Maintaining office supplies.
    • Providing professional and courteous customer service.
    • Assisting with the orientation/on the job training of new staff.
    • Completing work orders and contacting appropriate staff when requested for emergency repairs or special requests.
    • Inputting and extracting data of a highly technical nature.
    • Interpreting and transcribing doctors orders.
    • Maintaining patient records, scanning, quality control

    Work Schedule: 2 shifts available

    SHIFT 1: 7:30AM  4:00PM, Monday through Friday working every THIRD weekend with rotating holidays. Note: Dayshift position will provide backup coverage to Decedent Affairs, duties include but not limited to releasing deceased veterans to funeral homes, updating patient deaths, providing information regarding death benefits, updating Advance Directive information in patient records.

    SHIFT 2: 3:30PM  12Midnight, Monday-Friday working every OTHER weekend with rotating holidays.

    Functional Statement Title/#: Marketing Manager, GS-679-5

    Location:
    St. Louis, MO
    Company:
    Hallmark Cards
    Minimum Experience:
    1
    Match Score:
    95%

    Apply

    Email Marketing Manager

    Your Journey Points: 25

    BDubs Bot

    Big lists of job titles aren't the most helpful.

    Quick summaries of each job lead helps you make a more informed decision.

    Job Lead 1 of 11


    Email Marketing Manager

    San Franciso, CA - Uber Technologies


    They're looking for: Experience creating and launching email campaigns using a leading ESP such as ExactTarget and SendGrid.

    I'll be responsible for: Developing email marketing strategies that engage millions of users across the globe.

    I'll also be responsible for: Set-uping and deploying complex automated communications within ExactTarget and SendGrid

    I can expect to make: $59,600 Annual


    People who work here say: Super talented people are flocking to Uber from the Bay Area's top tech companies - Things move so much faster here than anywhere else I've worked - you'll be able to get much more done - Legitimately changing the world.

    They also say: Long hours (but if they feel like work, you're doing something wrong).

    The cost of living is about: $2.80/gal for gas, $1400/mo for rent (900 sq. ft), and $33 to go to dinner for two

    I may be promoted to: Senior Marketing Executive

    powered by


    Hint: Choosing 'Me' or 'Not Me' shows the next job lead.

    2. Brand Design - Beats by Dr. Dre

    Brand Design - Beats by Dr. Dre

    Your Journey Points: 30

    BDubs Bot

    Each time you engage with a job, I learn more and show you better ones.

    Job Lead 2 of 11


    Brand Design - Beats by Dr. Dre

    Culver City, CA - Apple, Inc.


    They're looking for: A student of consumers. Of trends, competitors and culture.

    I'll be responsible for: Design and deliver extraordinary brand marketing creative across all virtual and tangible spaces.

    I'll also be responsible for: Gather and tell stories that compel consumers to seek out Beats products.

    I can expect to make: $56,235


    People who work here say: There are limitless advancement opportunities. You work with some very cool people and the leadership cares about your development.

    They also say: The pay is excellent but the environment can be very stressful. Management is mostly competent and helpful, but a few bad eggs do make it through.

    The cost of living is about: $2.80/gal for gas, $1400/mo for rent (900 sq. ft), and $33 to go to dinner for two

    I may be promoted to: Senior Brand Executive

    powered by
